+
+Meet PortPulse in minutes with our ready-made Postman assets. This guide walks you through import, setup, and your first call—plus tips for CSV & ETag.
+
+:::tip TL;DR
+1) **Download** the collection (and optional environment). 2) **Import** into Postman. 3) **Set** `apiKey` and `baseUrl`. 4) **Send** a request.
+:::
+
+## Downloads
+
+- **Collection**: [portpulse-postman.json](/postman/portpulse-postman.json)
+- **Environment (optional)**: [portpulse.postman_environment.json](/postman/portpulse.postman_environment.json)
+
+> If downloads are blocked by policy, you can create the environment manually (below).
+
+## Prerequisites
+
+- A valid **API key** (see **[Authentication](/docs/Guides/authentication)**)
+- Postman app (Desktop recommended)
+- Base URL: `https://api.useportpulse.com`
+
+## Import the collection
+
+1. Open Postman → **Import**
+2. Drag & drop **`portpulse-postman.json`**, or pick it from disk
+3. The collection appears as **PortPulse API**
+
+## (Recommended) Environment
+
+### Option A — Import the provided environment
+1. **Import** `portpulse.postman_environment.json`
+2. Select the environment → **Edit** → set your values
+
+### Option B — Create it yourself
+Create **PortPulse – Prod** with variables:
+
+| Variable | Initial Value | Current Value | Notes |
+| --- | --- | --- | --- |
+| `baseUrl` | `https://api.useportpulse.com` | `https://api.useportpulse.com` | Change to staging if needed |
+| `apiKey`  | `pp_live_…` | `pp_live_…` | Your PortPulse API key |
+
+Click **Save**, then select the environment in the top-right switcher.
+
+:::note How variables are used
+Requests send `X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}` and target `{{baseUrl}}`. If you rename variables, update the collection or environment accordingly.
+:::
+
+## Your first call
+
+Try the **USLAX 30-day trend** example, or send a plain request:
+
+```http
+GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/ports/USLAX/trend?window=30&format=json
+X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
+```
+
+You should receive `200 OK` with JSON data. If not, see **Troubleshooting**.
+
+## CSV & ETag
+
+Some endpoints can return **CSV**. In Postman:
+
+- Use **Send and Download** to save locally
+- Prefer `If-None-Match` with an **ETag** to skip unchanged downloads  
+See: **[CSV & ETag](/docs/csv-etag)**.
+
+## Troubleshooting
+
+- **401 Unauthorized** → ensure header `X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}` and the variable is set
+- **429 Too Many Requests** → you’ve hit a quota/burst limit; see **[Rate limits](/docs/Guides/rate-limits)** and retry with backoff
+- **4xx/5xx** → compare with **[OpenAPI](/openapi)**, validate required params and formats
+- **Empty CSV** → try without `If-None-Match` to bypass cached ETag
